### Exception--> __init__.py

This file creates a custom exception system that provides detailed error messages instead of Python's default errors. It tells you what went wrong, where it happened, and on which line, making debugging much easier.


exc_info()
Returns three things:
(type, value, traceback)

Example:
_, _, exc_tb = sys.exc_info()

We only need the traceback (exc_tb).

